# Implementation Plan: Copy Pairing Command to Clipboard

## Summary
Add a "Copy" button in the action row and a `/copy` slash command that copies the external shell pairing command to the system clipboard using OSC 52 escape sequences (zero dependencies, works in most modern terminals including Ghostty, WezTerm, Alacritty, Kitty, iTerm2).

## Architecture Decision: OSC 52 (No New Crate)
OSC 52 is the right approach because:
- This is a crossterm/ratatui TUI running in raw mode — GUI clipboard crates (`arboard`, `cli-clipboard`) are unreliable in this context
- OSC 52 is a terminal escape sequence that tells the terminal emulator itself to set the clipboard
- All terminals in the candidate list (`resolve_terminal_executable`) support it: Ghostty, WezTerm, Alacritty, Kitty
- Zero new dependencies — just write bytes to stdout
- The app already uses `crossterm::execute!` to write to stdout

