## Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|------------|
| OSC 52 not supported by user's terminal | Copy silently fails | Show status message "copied (OSC 52)" so user knows it happened; they can manually copy from the log if their terminal is old |
| OSC 52 write during raw mode conflicts with ratatui rendering | Garbled output | Write to stdout with flush; crossterm raw mode doesn't block arbitrary escape sequences — this is safe. Could also write _between_ frames (the action handler runs outside `terminal.draw()`) |
| Pairing command not available (embedded mode) | Button does nothing | Already handled: the match arm checks `shell.external_connect_command()` and shows appropriate status message |
| Button hotkey collision | Character eaten during typing | Solved by not assigning a hotkey — mouse click + `/copy` command are sufficient |

